  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork tender, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590499760230-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590499760230-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590499760230-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590499760230-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590499760230-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Deseed the <strong>yellow pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop roughly</p><p>Chop the <strong>basil </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590499765498-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590499765498-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590499765498-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590499765498-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590499765498-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to the pan, with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>'Nduja</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the pepper is beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590499773075-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590499773075-x400.jpg",
